<font color="#FF0000">REPLY TO VIETSON</font><br>
<tt>Fri Jun  6 19:58:22 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Vietson,<br><br>
You present a very moving statement of a true dilemma. As I understand your comments, the Amerasians are caught in a cultural cross fire with no clear identity of their own.<br><br>
I agree with you that the Amerasians are victims of the war, and perhaps in a worse manner than most civilians. Not only did they experience the effects of the war, but were left hanging and excluded from whatever healing process occurred afterward.<br><br>
It is horrible to be alive and very human and be in such a position to be shunned by everyone through absolutely no fault of your own, and for reasons as perplexing as those of cultural or personal bias.<br><br>
Your idea of US Government support I am not sure will work. Private initiatives stand the best chance of success.<br><br>
I would like to speak with an Amerasian about the diffficulties you mention to better understand what is happening.<br><br>
Please e-mail me off line. I will respect your confidentiality. There is a Vietnamese Community within reach of me.
